1. Introduction
1.1 Higher Education and SUNY Buffalo State University
Higher education is a journey that involves several stages, including admission, enrollment, and
graduation. Each stage has its own set of challenges and opportunities. The journey through college
can be a transformative experience that shapes a students personal and professional life.
Colleges and universities serve as crucibles for intellectual growth, personal development, and the
cultivation of skills essential for future endeavors. SUNY Buffalo State University
1
, nestled in the
vibrant city of Buffalo, New York, exemplifies the transformative power of higher education. With
a commitment to academic excellence, Buffalo State stands as a testament to the profound impact
that institutions of higher learning can have on the lives of students.
1.2 Departmental Diversity
Buffalo State's academic landscape is characterized by a multitude of departments, each
contributing distinct disciplines. This diversity ensures a comprehensive educational experience,
fostering a well-rounded skill set among students.
1.3 Student Journey in Focus
For students, the college journey is marked by academic exploration, personal development, and
the acquisition of skills essential for future endeavors. Buffalo State's commitment to providing a
supportive learning environment ensures students navigate their academic journey with guidance
and resources.
1.4 The Role of Data Science in Higher Education
Data analysis has emerged as a powerful tool in higher education, enabling institutions to derive
meaningful insights for strategic planning. Analyzing the wealth of data generated by academic
offerings allows for informed decision-making, resource optimization, and an improved
understanding of student needs. This information can be used to make decisions about course
scheduling, staffing, and budget allocation. Students can also benefit from this analysis by having
access to a wider range of courses that are better suited to their interests and career goals.
1.5 Stakeholder Benefits
Data analysis serves as a crucial asset for authorities, decision-makers, and students alike.
Authorities gain insights for strategic planning, decision-makers optimize resource allocation, and
students benefit from personalized learning experiences and transparent academic pathways.
4
1.6 Scope of Analysis
This report focuses on a meticulous analysis of Buffalo State's undergraduate courses over the
years, specifically examining courses offered during the fall and spring semesters. By delving into
each department's course catalog, we aim to unravel trends, highlight academic strengths, and
provide valuable insights for those involved in educational planning.
As we embark on this data-driven exploration, the objective is to contribute factual insights that
enhance the understanding of Buffalo State's academic landscape and inform decision-making
processes.
5
2. Materials and Methodology
2.1 Data Source
The primary data source for this analysis is derived from web scraping Buffalo States official
course catalog information from the University Registrars page
2
. The data spans the years 2015
to 2023, encompassing the fall and spring semesters for each academic year.
2.2 Data Collection
Web scraping was implemented using Python's requests library to retrieve the HTML content
of the course catalog web pages. The BeautifulSoup library facilitated parsing and navigating
the HTML structure, enabling the extraction of essential information such as the course reference
number (CRN), catalog number (CatNum), department, year, and semester.
The data was systematically collected by iterating through the catalog pages for each academic
year and semester
3-20
. Each department's course information was extracted, providing a
comprehensive dataset for subsequent analysis.
2.3 Data Cleaning and Processing
The processing phase was implemented while ensuring the integrity and accuracy of the dataset.
No data cleaning was necessary since the raw dataframe obtained had no missing values. The
processed data was then structured into a Pandas DataFrame, facilitating efficient manipulation
and analysis in subsequent stages.
2.4 Analysis Framework
The analysis involved grouping the data by relevant parameters, specifically by year, semester, and
department. The objective was to quantify the number of unique courses offered in each
department during the fall and spring semesters across the specified years. The Pandas library was
instrumental in implementing the analysis framework, leveraging functionalities such as groupby
operations and unique value counting to derive meaningful insights.
2.5 Scope of Analysis
The scope of analysis includes an exploration of trends and patterns in Buffalo State's
undergraduate course offerings. The report focuses on presenting a comprehensive overview of the
number of courses offered by each department during the specified academic years, providing
users with valuable insights into the institution's academic landscape.
6
3. Data Analysis and Trends
3.1 Overview
This section aims to present an insightful analysis of Buffalo State College's undergraduate course
offerings to capture trends and patterns across the years 2015 to 2023. The analysis is segmented
by academic semesters (fall and spring) and explores the dynamics of both the number of
departments offering courses and the total course count.
3.2 Trends in Departmental Participation and Courses Offered
Figure 1 Number of Departments and Courses Oered
The stacked bar graph in Figure 1 illustrates the distribution of departments (left panel) offering
courses during the fall and spring semesters for each academic year, highlighting shifts in
participation over time.
Key Observations:
Notable fluctuations are observed, indicating potential shifts in academic focus.
The number of participating departments generally follows a downward trend.
The first drop in Departmental participation is noted in 2018, which stayed quite steady till
2022, followed by another drop.
7
The right-side panel of Figure 1 shows into the total number of courses offered, revealing the
magnitude of course offerings by participating departments over the specified years.
Key Observations:
A steady drop in the total number of courses is evident.
The largest drop has been from 2021 to 2022.
Fluctuations may signify dynamic changes in the curriculum. The necessity of minumul
enrolment [ 10 students] might play a role here.
3.3 In-Depth Analysis: The Impact of COVID-19 in 2020
The year 2020 marked a pivotal moment globally with the onset of the COVID-19 pandemic. The
effects of this unprecedented event reverberated across various sectors, including higher education.
Key Observations:
In Fall 2020, compared to previous year, there is a difference of only one department not
offering courses.
This number increased by 2 for the Spring of 2021, probably as online course offerings
rose in response to the pandemic.
In terms of the number of course offerings, there were fewer courses both in Fall 2020 as
well as Spring 2021 compared to previous years.
This downward trend continued till 2023.
The year 2020 witnessed unprecedented challenges globally due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
Buffalo State College, like many educational institutions, experienced disruptions in its academic
operations
21
. The decline in departmental participation and course offerings during this period can
be attributed to the institution's response to the pandemic. Adaptations such as remote learning,
altered academic schedules, and resource reallocation likely contributed to the observed trends
22
.
The institution's resilience in navigating these challenges underscores its commitment to
maintaining academic continuity in the face of external adversities.
3.4 Timeseries Analysis
Departments exhibit varying temporal engagements, with some consistently offering courses each
year, while others participate in more sporadic patterns. This temporal diversity in participation
underscores the fluidity and adaptability of the institution to changing educational needs.
Several departments established a continuous presence, contributing to the curriculum every
academic year from 2015 to 2023. In contrast, some departments initiated their course offerings in
8
later years, reflecting potential new academic initiatives or evolving departmental priorities. This
variability in the temporal dimension of course offerings is a key aspect of our timeseries analysis.
Departments displaying a narrower timespan of course offerings, such as from 2015 to 2017 or
2015 to 2021, reveal distinct phases of engagement. These patterns might signify specific
programmatic focuses or transient academic emphases during those years.
The introduction of courses by certain departments in 2022 is particularly noteworthy. This
includes Data Science courses. This temporal alignment could signal a concerted effort to expand
academic offerings, introducing fresh perspectives and areas of study to the Buffalo State
curriculum.

3.5 Strategic Dynamics
3.5.1 Departments With More Than 1000 Total Course Sections
This analysis focuses on delineating the academic contributions of Buffalo State College's departments,
specifically examining the departmental performers in terms of total course sections offered during the
period from 2015 to 2023. Employing a rigorous data-driven methodology, our objective is to move beyond
numerical representations, aiming for a nuanced understanding of the trajectories carved by these
departments over the specified timeframe.
In particular, the departments of Music, English and Mathematics are leading, followed by Business,
Communication and History & Social Studies Education. Notably, two of the six have more than 2000 total
course sections in this timeframe.
Figure 3 Top 10 Departments in total course secon oerings
Noteworthy Trends:
Consistent Pioneers: These departments consistently demonstrate leadership in academic
contributions, sustaining their prominence in offering a significant number of course
sections throughout the entire timeframe.
Diverse Engagement: The sustained high course section count suggests both adaptability
and robust academic offerings.
10
3.5.2 Departments With Less Than 100 Total Course Sections
This section turns the spotlight on departments at Buffalo State College that have contributed less
than 100 total course sections from 2015 to 2023. Utilizing a rigorous data-driven methodology,
this analysis seeks to move beyond mere numerical representations and cultivate a nuanced
understanding of the academic trajectories charted by these departments during the specified
timeframe.
Of note, the Data Science and Analytics as well as Data Analytics and Mathematics departments
have only offered 2 undergraduate course sections in the past two years.
Figure 4 Departments Oering Less Than A Total Of 100 Course Secons
Offering less than 100 courses over a span of nine years could indicate several noteworthy aspects
about a department's academic profile:
1. Specialization and Focus: Departments with a limited number of courses may signify a
focused academic approach, emphasizing specialization in particular subject areas. This
can be indicative of a deliberate strategy to excel in a niche field.
2. Resource Allocation: A lower course count may suggest efficient resource allocation,
directing faculty expertise and resources towards a select set of courses. This targeted
approach can lead to high-quality instruction and student engagement in specific subject
domains.
3. Strategic Planning: Departments offering a modest number of courses may be engaging
in strategic planning, aligning their academic offerings with institutional goals, student
11
demand, and faculty expertise. This intentional approach ensures that each course serves a
clear purpose within the department's overall objectives.
4. Faculty Expertise: A focused course selection could reflect the department's faculty
expertise. Departments may choose to concentrate on areas where their faculty members
excel, ensuring a high standard of instruction and academic rigor.
5. Collaborative Initiatives: Departments with fewer courses may engage in collaborative
initiatives with other departments or interdisciplinary programs. This collaborative
approach could lead to innovative and cross-disciplinary courses that contribute to a well-
rounded educational experience.
6. Adaptability: Offering fewer courses might indicate an ability to adapt to changing
educational landscapes. Departments may streamline their offerings to meet evolving
student needs, industry demands, or emerging trends in academia.
Alternative Perspective: Implications of Limited Course Offerings:
1. Resource Allocation: Departments offering fewer courses may face resource constraints,
impacting faculty availability, infrastructure, or funding. This raises questions about the
equitable distribution of resources across departments.
2. Program Viability: Limited course offerings may indicate challenges in sustaining or
expanding academic programs within a department. This could prompt a closer evaluation
of the program's viability, relevance, and alignment with student demand.
3. Diversity of Offerings: A low number of course sections may limit students' choices and
exposure to a variety of subjects. Departments with fewer offerings might benefit from
exploring ways to diversify their course catalog to cater to diverse academic interests.
4. Impact on Student Engagement: The availability of a broad range of courses enhances
students' academic experiences. Departments offering fewer courses may need to assess
how this impacts student engagement, satisfaction, and overall academic enrichment.
5. Strategic Planning: Departments with limited course offerings may need to engage in
strategic planning to address the root causes. This could involve exploring new academic
collaborations, seeking external funding, or re-evaluating the department's academic focus.
6. Impact on Departmental Reputation: A consistently low number of course sections may
influence the perceived academic robustness of a department. This aspect is crucial for
attracting prospective students, faculty, and fostering a positive reputation within the
institution.
It might be worthwhile to assess both perspectives and all above factors in the broader context of
the institution's goals, the specific academic mission of the department, and the preferences and
needs of the student population. A lower course count does not inherently imply a lack of impact
or significance; instead, it may underscore a department's strategic and intentional approach to
academic delivery.
12
3.6 Comparative Analysis
This section compares the Music Department with the DSA (Data Science and Analytics) and
DAM (Data Analytics and Mathematics) Departments at Buffalo State from 2015 to 2023. We
analyzed the number of course sections offered during fall and spring semesters to understand the
distinctive patterns of these departments. This comparison provides straightforward insights into
their roles and impact.
Figure 5 Comparave Analysis
Figure 5 presents a comparative overview of course sections offered by the Music Department in
contrast to the DSA and DAM Departments at Buffalo State.
Key Observations:
1. Music Department Dominance: The Music Department emerges as a prominent
contributor, consistently offering the highest number of course sections throughout the
specified period. This sustained dominance underscores the department's robust academic
presence and its integral role in Buffalo State's educational landscape.
2. DSA and DAM Departments: In comparison, the DSA and DAM Departments have a
distinctive pattern. Both departments exhibit a parallel trajectory in terms of course
offerings, with a see-saw pattern in course sections in from 2020 2023. This synchronous
trend suggests a potential collaborative initiative or shared academic focus during these
years.
13
Noteworthy Instances:
In 2020 and 2021, DAM offered one course section each in the in the spring semester. This
suggests a deliberate choice to maintain a minimal yet impactful presence during these
specific academic terms.
In 2022 and 2023, the DSA department expanded their course offerings to include one
course section each in both fall and spring semesters. This simultaneous growth may
signify an intentional effort to diversify and channel their academic efforts.
Interpretation:
While the Music Department stands out for its sustained prominence, the coordinated patterns
observed in the DSA and DAM Departments indicate strategic adjustments in course offerings.
These adjustments may align with evolving academic priorities, student demand, or collaborative
endeavors between the two departments. The figure provides a visual representation of the
dynamic academic landscape, offering valuable insights into the course section trends across these
key departments.
14
4. Summary
The exploration of Buffalo State College's undergraduate academic landscape over the years has
unearthed intricate patterns, revealing the dynamic interplay of departments and courses. Key
observations highlight the academic prowess of the Music Department, consistently leading with
the highest course sectionsa testament to its enduring role in shaping the institution's educational
narrative.
Fluctuations in departmental participation suggest potential shifts in academic focus, with notable
drops in 2018 and 2022. The total number of courses exhibits a steady decline, emphasizing the
dynamic nature of the curriculum and potential considerations like minimal enrollment
requirements.
Noteworthy instances punctuate specific years, such as DAM's deliberate choice of maintaining a
minimal yet impactful presence in 2020 and 2021. In contrast, the DSA department strategically
expanded its course offerings in 2022 and 2023, signaling a deliberate effort to diversify its
academic contributions. Examining the temporal dimension unveils consistent pioneers and
diverse engagement. Some departments sustain leadership in academic contributions, displaying
adaptability and robust offerings throughout the entire timeframe. Concurrently, varied
engagement spans, such as from 2015 to 2017 or 2015 to 2021, denote distinct phases of
departmental involvement, revealing potential programmatic focuses or transient academic
emphases.
This comprehensive analysis delves into Buffalo State's academic curriculum, unraveling trends,
patterns, and shifts that contribute to a nuanced understanding of the institution's educational
evolution. As Buffalo State continues its journey, these insights might provide a foundation for
informed decision-making, strategic planning, student academic planning and career development,
and fostering a vibrant academic environment.
15
5. Conclusion
The application of data science skills plays a pivotal role in advancing our understanding of
academic landscapes
23
. The systematic acquisition and refinement of data form the groundwork
for comprehensive analysis. Techniques such as exploratory data analysis provide insights into
temporal trends, offering a nuanced perspective on the evolution of academic offerings over the
years. Time series analysis becomes instrumental in uncovering the dynamics of course sections,
revealing patterns in departmental engagements.
Visualizations, carefully designed through data science skills, become a means to communicate
complex information effectively, providing a detailed narrative within the academic data. Beyond
technical aspects, data science promotes interdisciplinary insights, fostering collaboration across
departments. In the context of Buffalo State's academic analysis, data science can serve as a
guiding force, translating raw data into actionable intelligence for educators, administrators, and
students. This data-driven exploration not only presents numerical findings but also empowers
institutions to make the right decisions and strategically adapt to the changing landscape of higher
education.
